annotationA: Spaghetti squash (sqh) is the regulatory light chain of the nonmuscle type 2 myosin. Its phosphorylation through the Rho-Rho Kinase pathway is predicted to activate myosin motor activity. Sqh and myosin function in cellular processes such as cytokinesis, and also contribute to tissue morphogenesis
annotationB: Myosin-2 essential light chain; Protein binding; calcium ion binding; myosin binding; myosin heavy chain binding. It is involved in the biological process described with: actin filament-based movement
